abstract: CHICAGO, April 2.--The McCaull Opera Company opened a four weeks' engagement at the Chicago Opera House to-night, presenting "The Begum," which is to be given for the first week. abstract: The steamship Chateau Margaux, which sailed from this port for Bordeaux last Friday, returned yesterday, having in tow the steamship California. On Saturday she was picked up by the Chateau Margaux 275 miles east of Sandy Hook.

abstract: CHICAGO, April 27.--To-morrow the issue of the Alarm, the paper of which A.R. Parsons, the Anarchist, was editor, will be suspended indefinitely.
